1
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:38,133
Stop!

2
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:39,767
I said stop!

3
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:42,433
- Doctor, help me!
- What happened?

4
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:43,500
He pushed me.

5
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,300
Doc, how is the baby?

6
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:47,167
I've seen it in his eyes.

7
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,667
Manuel loves my baby.

8
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,233
Here, sis.

9
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,433
Drink this.

10
00:00:52,567 --> 00:00:56,000
You must fight for the kids'
rights to their father.

11
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:56,633
Hello?

12
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,967
So, how's my former love?

13
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:02,500
You know that I don't love her,
you're the one I love.

14
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:05,467
Didn't I tell you to stop
calling Manuel?

15
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,767
I'm the first Mrs. Cruz!

16
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,800
Oh well! He married me!

17
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:11,333
He is the father
of my children.

18
00:01:11,467 --> 00:01:13,100
Your relationship with him
is over.

19
00:01:22,867 --> 00:01:26,933
My gosh! The nerve
of that woman!

20
00:01:27,067 --> 00:01:28,367
What did she want to happen?

21
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:31,533
She wants you to cut the
connection with Manuel?

22
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:35,333
What about the child
support for your kids?

23
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:37,333
I guess so.

24
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:38,800
And you agreed to it?

25
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:43,400
I tried to fight for my rights.

26
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:45,667
But I can't do anything
about it.

27
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,433
Sis! You can do something
about it!

28
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:56,300
Call Manuel and tell
him what she told you!

29
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:58,733
And then what?

30
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,833
Hazel won't leave me alone!

31
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:07,467
So what now? You'll give up just
like that?

32
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,967
What about your rights?

33
00:02:11,367 --> 00:02:12,500
What about the children?

34
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:13,833
What's gonna happen to you now?

35
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:17,900
You want me to fight for Manuel?

36
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:24,267
How can I fight for someone
who couldn't fight for me?

37
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,500
Hazel is right.

38
00:02:36,433 --> 00:02:38,433
She has the right,
he married her.

39
00:02:40,367 --> 00:02:41,733
he married her.

40
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:48,167
And I can't do anything
about it.

41
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:51,467
And my kids got dragged
into this mess too.

42
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,333
Sis.

43
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:57,900
What are you going to do now?

44
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:44,700
Why are you still awake?

45
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,200
Is it because of the baby?

46
00:03:49,967 --> 00:03:52,133
No, I just used the bathroom.

47
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,500
Go back to sleep.

48
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:44,433
Wait baby.

49
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:56,500
Okay, mommy's here.

50
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,600
Oh no, you're all wet.

51
00:04:58,733 --> 00:05:00,300
Come on, sweetie, I'll change
your diaper.

52
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:02,067
You're all wet.

53
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:09,767
Wait, sweetie!

54
00:05:31,567 --> 00:05:33,133
Sweetie, wait?

55
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:03,333
Where's your prescription?

56
00:06:03,467 --> 00:06:04,967
I'll get the medicine for you.

57
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,867
It's on the fridge door.

58
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:10,067
Is there anything else you need?

59
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:16,867
Manuel, if you want, I can
manage your salary.

60
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,800
I will do the budgeting.
I'm good at that.

61
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:23,833
I'm going to send money
to the Philippines.

62
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,667
Is it an emergency?

63
00:06:30,467 --> 00:06:35,467
If it's not urgent, perhaps you
can prioritize our baby for now.

64
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:09,767
Hush baby.

65
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,167
Don't cry, sweetie.

66
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:17,300
Here baby.

67
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,900
Why isn't she answering?

68
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:29,567
Coleen, Coleen!

69
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:35,300
Mom!

70
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:39,333
Why are you not
tending to her?

71
00:08:41,733 --> 00:08:43,600
Did you drink again?

72
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:45,533
Oh Mom!

73
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:59,033
I'm glad Coleen didn't get hurt.

74
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:03,000
She could've gotten hurt, right?

75
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,400
Why are you drinking?

76
00:09:07,933 --> 00:09:09,433
It helps me out, Sweetie.

77
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:12,767
At least...

78
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:14,867
even just for a moment.

79
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:18,300
It makes me forget,

80
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,367
what your father did to us
for a bit.

81
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,333
I don't know how to start again.

82
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:33,833
I need to make longganisa.

83
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:35,567
I have incoming orders.

84
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:38,867
But whenever
I think about your dad.

85
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:41,700
That he won't be
coming back to us.

86
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:45,200
It makes me feel weak.

87
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:49,667
Oh...

88
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:54,400
I remember those times...

89
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:58,400
before he left for work...

90
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:02,700
he helped me out with
the household chores.

91
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:07,033
He helps me with Coleen.

92
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,200
When he went to Saudi Arabia,

93
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:15,733
there's not a day that
he doesn't call me.

94
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,533
I don't ever feel like
I'm alone.

95
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:20,667
He's always with me.

96
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:24,100
I have a partner.

97
00:10:26,133 --> 00:10:28,200
But now...

98
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,333
Now, he's gone.

99
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,533
He's gone, sweetie.

100
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,433
I can't talk to him anymore.

101
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:42,000
You miss him, don't you?

102
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,400
I miss him too.

103
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,733
If you want...

104
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:54,200
we can call him.

105
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:57,933
Tell him to come home.

106
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,600
We can't do that, sweetie.

107
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,500
We can't do that.

108
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,667
Hazel called me.

109
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:17,133
She forbade me from
talking to your dad.

110
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,733
We can't ask him to come home.

111
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:24,467
He has a home there now.

112
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,767
We're not his home anymore.

113
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,833
Sweetie...

114
00:11:30,967 --> 00:11:33,200
I hope you can understand your
Mom.

115
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:38,500
When I drink.

116
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,867
I just have a lot to do.

117
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:45,900
I'm struggling...

118
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,467
becase I'm doing everything
alone.

119
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:55,267
Mom...

120
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,367
I here for you.

121
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:00,900
I will help you.

122
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,367
Don't cry.

123
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:26,033
Is he going to let you hold
his salary?

124
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:29,200
Oh, yes.

125
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:30,833
You know me.

126
00:12:30,967 --> 00:12:31,900
Isn't it obvious?

127
00:12:32,033 --> 00:12:34,200
My pretending
to be nice is working.

128
00:12:35,533 --> 00:12:37,333
You don't need to take his
money.

129
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,367
You make money anyway.

130
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,000
And you make more money
than he does.

131
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:45,767
Alice, it's not about the money.

132
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,700
Can't you see?

133
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,600
As long as he supports them.

134
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:52,100
He won't cut connection with
Felma.

135
00:12:52,633 --> 00:12:55,567
Before I know it,
I won't have a husband anymore.

136
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,467
You sound like a jealous wife.

137
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:02,333
Don't tell me you're falling in
love with your husband

138
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,133
It's possible.

139
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:15,600
Especially now that
I see how kind he is,

140
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:19,933
how affectionate and caring
he is with me and my baby.

141
00:13:21,633 --> 00:13:23,600
That's why I need to keep
an eye on him.

142
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:28,233
I need to cut his connection
with Felma as early as now.

143
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:33,000
Oh my gosh, sis.

144
00:13:33,533 --> 00:13:37,700
I get you, that's
why we're such good friends.

145
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,267
Jeffrey...

146
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,367
can you watch Coleen for now?

147
00:13:53,967 --> 00:13:55,333
I just need to review for
my exam.

148
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,633
Didn't you see that
I just got home?

149
00:13:58,267 --> 00:13:59,800
Where's Mom?

150
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,700
She's resting right now.

151
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,467
She's drunk again.

152
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,100
What's for lunch?

153
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:12,933
I'm hungry.

154
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:17,633
Oh my...

155
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:26,800
There's no rice?

156
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,733
How can I make rice, Jeffrey?

157
00:14:30,867 --> 00:14:33,500
Can't you see that
I'm taking care of Coleen?

158
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:34,700
Why don't you make the rice?

159
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,633
There's nothing here to cook.

160
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:43,033
What are we going to do now,
Jeffrey?

161
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:45,633
What are we going
to eat for lunch?

162
00:14:57,667 --> 00:14:58,667
Here's my payment.

163
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,300
- Here's my payment.
- Thank you.

164
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:10,400
Mrs. Cora.

165
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:13,900
Can I have three pieces of
tilapia?

166
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:15,733
You're putting it
on your tab again?

167
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:19,067
Jeffrey, you owe me
a lot of money already.

168
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,967
Your mom is not paying for it.

169
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:22,633
I will let my mom know.

170
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:24,733
Go tell her to pay now,
before you put more on the tab.

171
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:26,433
Mrs. Cora...

172
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,467
I'm hungry.

173
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,400
No way! You have to pay me
first!

174
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,967
Mrs. Cora, can we have more
rice?

175
00:15:35,133 --> 00:15:35,967
Wait a minute.

176
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,900
Just put this on our tab,
Mrs. Cora!

177
00:15:38,033 --> 00:15:39,900
- Thank you!
- Hey you!

178
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:48,400
Jeffrey,

179
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,233
where did you get this from?

180
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:54,100
From Mrs. Cora's store.

181
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:57,600
I'm glad she let you put
it on our tab.

182
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:12,100
She wants me to tell you
to pay what we owe her.

183
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:17,500
I will, once I collect the money
for the longganisa.

184
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:21,033
But...

185
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:23,533
you haven't made
any longganisa yet.

186
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,800
Don't worry, I'll help you out.

187
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:36,233
I will do it.

188
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:38,533
I will keep my promise to Dad.

189
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:40,900
<i>Jeffrey, don't forget
what I said...</i>

190
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:43,867
<i>Jeffrey, you will be the pillar
of the family for now.</i>

191
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:47,400
<i>You have to help your mom
and siblings.</i>

192
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:49,933
Take good care of them.
Do you understand?

193
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:51,000
Yes, Dad.

194
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,267
Can we not talk about someone
who's not here right now?

195
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:01,333
Go ahead, eat your lunch.

196
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:53,333
Hazel.

197
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,400
- Hazel, here's your medicine.
- Hey.

198
00:17:57,533 --> 00:17:58,567
You're home on time.

199
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,567
I also got you
your favorite kebab.

200
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,333
- Wow.
- It will give you an appetite.

201
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,033
To feed our baby.

202
00:18:05,733 --> 00:18:08,400
My husband is so thoughtful.

203
00:18:08,533 --> 00:18:10,033
I'll just send money back
to the Philippines

204
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:11,333
on my next salary.

205
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:21,700
Manuel,

206
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:25,033
if you're going to send money
back to the Philippines,

207
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,567
you won't have much left
from your salary.

208
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,533
Don't you have to pay
off your debt, too?

209
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,167
There won't be anything
left for me and the baby.

210
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,133
We need your help too.

211
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:46,033
Ouch.

212
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:48,767
Why?

213
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,900
The baby just kicked.

214
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:58,767
Here, feel it.

215
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:00,933
Did you feel it?

216
00:19:01,067 --> 00:19:02,467
That's a strong one!

217
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:07,700
- It's moving.
- She's all over the place!

218
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,400
Hi, baby.

219
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:12,100
It's me, daddy.

220
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,733
Don't move too much, baby.

221
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:30,633
Andrea!

222
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:47,633
What?

223
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:50,567
That's impossible!

224
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:53,033
My daughter is not capable of
cheating

225
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,667
She's an honor student.

226
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,800
She studied hard for the exam.

227
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,200
I couldn't believe it either.

228
00:19:58,333 --> 00:20:01,400
This is the first time that
your daughter has cheated.

229
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,967
Is that true, Sweetie?

230
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,533
Why did you cheat?

231
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:13,167
Because I didn't get to study
for my exam, Mom.

232
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:16,333
Because I was taking care of
Coleen.

233
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:19,833
Why didn't you tell me
you have an exam?

234
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:22,133
I could have taken care of
your sister.

235
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:26,700
How are you going to do that
when you're always tired?

236
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:30,333
And drunk.

237
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,033
Andrea, can you go outside
for now?

238
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,833
I need to talk to your mom.

239
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,467
Okay.

240
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:49,600
Mrs. Cruz, I didn't want
to meddle in your affairs.

241
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:53,133
But what might be the reason for
your daughter to act like that?

242
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:57,033
Ma'am, aren't you being too
personal?

243
00:20:57,167 --> 00:20:58,800
I'm just concerned for
your daughter.

244
00:20:58,933 --> 00:21:02,233
The children get affected,

245
00:21:02,367 --> 00:21:04,867
when their parents have
domestic problems.

246
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,233
Just like now.

247
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:11,100
I admit, I had a drink or two.
Is that wrong?

248
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,333
- Mrs. Cruz.
- Can you stop

249
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:15,533
calling me Mrs. Cruz?

250
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:18,567
You don't know what I'm going
through right now!

251
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:20,133
What is troubling you?

252
00:21:20,267 --> 00:21:24,367
Perhaps I could help you and
your daughter.

253
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:27,733
Are you saying that
I'm a bad mother?

254
00:21:28,133 --> 00:21:30,033
That I can't take care of
my children?

255
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:32,833
Ma'am, all my life,

256
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:35,833
I've done nothing but
take care of my children.

257
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:37,500
So don't you dare judge me!

258
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:39,333
I think it's best
if you go home for now.

259
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:42,500
We can talk late
when you're sober.

260
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:44,133
I'm not drunk!

261
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,233
My mind is clear.

262
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:50,633
You really want to know
my problem?

263
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:52,967
My husband left us!

264
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:56,100
He abandoned me and my children
to be with another woman!

265
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:57,733
That's my problem!

266
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,233
What are you looking at?

267
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:03,167
The nerve...

268
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:08,667
Andrea?

269
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,600
Andrea!

270
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,867
We're gonna make you
a bottle of milk, okay?

271
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:05,500
Hello?

272
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,300
<i> Dad?</i>

273
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:09,667
Andrea? Why are you crying?

274
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:13,567
I miss you so much.

275
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:17,700
I've been wanting to call you,

276
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:21,667
but Mom said
we're not allowed to.

277
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,100
What?
Who said that?

278
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:26,667
That's not true, sweetie.

279
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,400
But Mom said...

280
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:33,533
your wife called her.

281
00:23:34,133 --> 00:23:38,067
She forbade us from calling you.

282
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:41,400
Daddy, please come home.

283
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:43,233
Who are you talking to?
Are you talking to your dad?

284
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:45,333
Didn't I tell you not
to talk to him anymore?

285
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:46,900
- Mom, give that back!
- Hello?

286
00:23:47,033 --> 00:23:49,133
- I'm still talking to my dad!
- Hello, Andrea?

287
00:23:49,267 --> 00:23:50,867
- Shut up!
- Mom,

288
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,100
Mom, what's going on?

289
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:52,933
<i> Hello?</i>

290
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,500
Hello? Andrea!

291
00:23:57,733 --> 00:24:00,033
I told her not to call your dad!

292
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:01,633
And she disobeyed me!

293
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:06,800
But dad told me that
I can call him anytime.

294
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:09,000
What if his wife
answers the phone?

295
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:11,033
She forbade us from calling him,
remember?

296
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:13,700
I just want to ask for help

297
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,700
I will ask him to come home.

298
00:24:17,267 --> 00:24:19,133
So you won't get drunk anymore.

299
00:24:19,267 --> 00:24:23,567
So that I can study and
don't have to cheat!

300
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,167
Did you cheat on your exam?

301
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:29,000
There.

302
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:30,900
Talk to your sister!

303
00:24:31,033 --> 00:24:34,233
Why aren't you helping her?

304
00:24:34,367 --> 00:24:36,167
To take care Coleen.

305
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:39,767
Mom, we have a varsity game.

306
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,200
You're prioritizing your game?

307
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:45,600
You know that we're in
a messy situation right now!

308
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:48,133
I'm doing everything I can.

309
00:24:48,267 --> 00:24:50,367
As far as my strength
can take me!

310
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:54,167
And now you're telling your dad,
what's going on here!

311
00:24:54,733 --> 00:24:56,367
What if Hazel answered
the phone?

312
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:58,300
Do you think
she'll give him back?

313
00:24:58,433 --> 00:25:00,533
Do you think
she'll feel bad for us?

314
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:02,533
Do you think she'll let us have
your dad back?

315
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:03,700
No, she won't!

316
00:25:09,333 --> 00:25:11,800
That woman brought me down!

317
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:17,967
Please, don't let her trample
all over me!

318
00:25:20,267 --> 00:25:21,800
So don't ever call him again!

319
00:25:22,067 --> 00:25:22,933
Do you understand that?

320
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:26,033
Let me at least have my dignity!

321
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:57,633
I'm going to pick up
the longganisa.

322
00:25:57,767 --> 00:25:58,867
I ordered one kilo.

323
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,300
Okay.
I'll get it for you.

324
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,367
Mrs. Lin, I'm sorry,

325
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:04,067
but my mom hasn't made them yet.

326
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,833
What's going on with your mom?

327
00:26:05,967 --> 00:26:07,533
She's being irresponsible!

328
00:26:08,433 --> 00:26:11,933
You said you love me, Manuel?

329
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:18,333
Why can't you fight for me?

330
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:21,667
Thief! He took my wallet!

331
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,467
He took my wallet! Help!
Thief!

332
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,600
Get out of there!

333
00:26:24,933 --> 00:26:26,400
Miss! What are you doing?

334
00:26:26,667 --> 00:26:27,833
You're the one who ran me over,

335
00:26:27,967 --> 00:26:29,000
but you have the guts to act
arrogant.

336
00:26:29,300 --> 00:26:30,967
Why did Felma get summoned to
the Barangay office?

337
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:33,933
Felma damaged a car.

338
00:26:34,067 --> 00:26:36,433
If I don't pay
the car owner for the damage,

339
00:26:36,567 --> 00:26:38,767
The owner will sue her!
